Lufthansa Suspends Tokyo Flights, Rerouting Its Planes to Osaka, Nagoya

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-03-15T11:18:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/lufthansa-suspends-all-tokyo-flights-reroutes-services-to-osaka-nagoya.html
  Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA)  said it’s
suspended flights to and from  Tokyo  and is rerouting planes to
Nagoya and  Osaka  instead. The airline’s flights are stopping in  Seoul  to change crews to avoid having staff stay overnight in  Japan , spokesman  Thomas Jachnow  said in a telephone interview
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
